479
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:12,620
I respect the Admiral.

480
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:18,500
Maybe we should talk about Troy then, and Harmony, and Codebreakers.

481
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:21,280
Herzog, I demand to know your source.

482
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:24,660
Yes, a security breach that major is worrying, isn't it?

483
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:27,100
But it was just a supposition on my part.

484
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:30,600
And some basic investigation a schoolgirl could do.

485
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:32,280
Who have you got working on this?

486
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:33,640
One of your moles?

487
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:37,200
Some low-level parasite in someone else's department?

488
00:17:37,620 --> 00:17:39,860
Isn't that your standard operating procedure?

489
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:43,880
It's always useful to meet with you, Standish.

490
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,960
That's y'all a face, right?

491
00:17:47,580 --> 00:17:49,240
A schoolgirl, Herzog?

492
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:51,580
Harvey, old friend, you're right.

493
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:53,320
I am too old for this.

494
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:56,400
I'm good at plugging leaks, old man.

495
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:03,000
Careful, that's a tombstone.

496
00:18:03,860 --> 00:18:06,340
Easy to trip over in the dark.

497
00:18:06,980 --> 00:18:08,360
I'll remember that.

