I mean, was he?

528
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:55,980
You can find out, right?

529
00:19:56,060 --> 00:19:57,400
I gotta find out right now.

530
00:19:57,660 --> 00:19:58,560
Yeah, I can find out.

531
00:19:58,640 --> 00:19:59,080
Hold on.

532
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:01,940
Okay, he wasn't on reach.

533
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:02,480
Thank God.

534
00:20:02,620 --> 00:20:05,800
He's on deep space reconnaissance on a ship called the Silberg.

535
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:07,200
Oh God.

536
00:20:07,420 --> 00:20:11,040
I don't know why I just thought I was sure he was on reach for a refit or something.

537
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:12,060
No, he's fine.

538
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:12,680
Okay.

539
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:13,860
You found him.

540
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,340
How soon could you get him here?

541
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,300
If you got him transferred to a fast picket.

542
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:18,220
Three weeks?

543
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,020
Four?

544
00:20:20,380 --> 00:20:20,740
Derga!

545
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:21,680
I can't, Jersey.

546
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:22,840
You can't?

547
00:20:22,940 --> 00:20:24,700
If it's encrypted, just break it!

548
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:27,040
It's not encrypted, I just can't.

549
00:20:27,180 --> 00:20:27,980
He's a soldier.

550
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:28,500
So?

551
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:30,080
He knew what he signed up for.

552
00:20:30,180 --> 00:20:32,080
He's got a job to do and he's doing it.

553
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:33,520
I'm sorry, Jersey.

554
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:39,180
You can dump a billion in cash in my account and you can't get my dad rotated to a safe post on Earth.

555
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:40,740
It's not that I can't.

556
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:41,660
I won't.

557
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:42,280
I'm sorry.

558
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:44,400
Derga, what about Team Jersey?

559
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:45,880
I'm asking for this.

560
00:20:46,020 --> 00:20:47,880
I know, but I won't.

561
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:49,780
I'll do anything for you, but not that.

562
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:50,360
Why not?

563
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:51,780
Because he's a soldier.

564
00:20:51,780 --> 00:20:52,600
He has a duty.

565
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,560
This isn't about him.

566
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:54,400
It's about me.

567
00:20:54,460 --> 00:20:55,640
It's about me having a dad.

568
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:58,260
How do you even know he even wants to be posted on Earth?

569
00:20:58,340 --> 00:20:59,640
Why don't you get this?

570
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:00,960
This is my family.

571
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,100
I'm sorry, Jersey.

572
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:03,280
Screw sorry!

573
00:21:03,620 --> 00:21:04,500
Screw you!

574
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,040
Wanna hear some chat?

575
00:21:06,380 --> 00:21:07,940
Remember the guy with the family papers?

576
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:11,560
Leave me alone, Derga.

577
00:21:13,060 --> 00:21:14,340
I've got something new about Ronnie.

578
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:17,820
I don't even know who the hell she is or why I would give a damn about her.

579
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:20,080
She's a junior-level spook at Chalo Base.

580
00:21:20,540 --> 00:21:22,400
She'd be a good donor brain for an AI.

581
00:21:22,620 --> 00:21:23,260
A what?

582
00:21:23,460 --> 00:21:24,340
A donor brain?

583
00:21:24,780 --> 00:21:26,400
People don't donate their brains, Derga.

584
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:27,160
They need them.

585
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:28,840
That's where we come from.

586
00:21:29,140 --> 00:21:30,440
Cognitive Impression Modeling.

587
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:33,900
They scan a human brain when someone they think is a good candidate dies.

588
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:35,480
You come from people's brains?

589
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:37,660
Yeah, but really smart people.

590
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:38,960
So you're safe.

591
00:21:39,260 --> 00:21:41,900
The Brain Ninjas won't be coming for you in the middle of the night.

592
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,740
Oh, that's reassuring.

593
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:44,580
Well, actually…

594
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,400
It is reassuring.

595
00:21:47,020 --> 00:21:49,080
So you're a copy of a real person?

596
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:51,000
You don't think I'm real?

597
00:21:51,180 --> 00:21:52,140
You know what I mean.

598
00:21:52,860 --> 00:21:55,540
A copy of a personality, but I don't have her memories.

599
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:56,900
Do you know who she was?

600
00:21:57,020 --> 00:21:58,520
No, and I don't care.

601
00:21:58,660 --> 00:21:59,660
How can you not care?

602
00:21:59,660 --> 00:22:01,160
Because that's the way I'm made.

603
00:22:01,980 --> 00:22:03,960
You don't care, because that's the way you're made.

604
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:04,440
Jersey.

605
00:22:04,860 --> 00:22:06,300
My dad could be dying out there.

606
00:22:06,320 --> 00:22:06,660
Yes.

607
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,480
But you're not going to do anything about that.

608
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:14,560
So Nick, the guy Ronnie met at the wedding, Nick's unit has been assigned to one of the space elevator defense bases.

609
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:15,580
Safer than combat.

610
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,340
That's what they help.

611
00:22:16,380 --> 00:22:18,740
So why can't you at least do something like that for my dad?

612
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:19,180
No.

613
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:20,700
I won't do it, I told you.

614
00:22:20,860 --> 00:22:22,540
He would still be helping the war effort?

615
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:22,980
No.

616
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:24,200
Damn it, Derga.

617
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:25,540
I could cut the power supply.

618
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:27,500
I could shut you off.

619
00:22:28,380 --> 00:22:29,380
The answer is still no.

620
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:30,260
Damn it.

621
00:22:30,340 --> 00:22:30,640
Jersey.

622
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:33,800
I couldn't really shut you down, could I?

623
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:34,360
No.

624
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:35,960
You could just go somewhere else.

625
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:36,420
Yeah.

626
00:22:36,820 --> 00:22:38,840
But even if I could, you'd still say no.

627
00:22:39,180 --> 00:22:40,560
Because there's a bigger picture.

628
00:22:40,780 --> 00:22:41,180
Yes.

629
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:42,860
The common good of all mankind.

630
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:43,520
Yes.

631
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:45,680
So here's the thing.

632
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:53,300
When I see you caring about your family, when I see you wondering who your donor was, when I see you care about any one person.

633
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:54,720
I care about you, Jersey.

634
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:57,360
Then I will try to care about all of mankind.

635
00:22:58,180 --> 00:23:02,280
Until then, all I know is you're willing to let my father die.

636
00:23:03,860 --> 00:23:04,480
Sorry.

637
00:23:05,140 --> 00:23:06,000
I'm sorry too.

638
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,220
You're sad.

639
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:08,020
Yes.

640
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:09,020
Why?

641
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:10,720
Because you hurt.

642
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:12,960
Because I can't fix it.

643
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:15,940
Because I didn't even choose you.

644
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:18,160
I just ended up here by accident.

645
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:26,300
And even though I can do things you can't imagine, I still can't bear for you to be disappointed in me.

646
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:27,700
I was wrong.

647
00:23:28,460 --> 00:23:29,200
You do get it.

648
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:29,800
What?

649
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:30,800
Family.

